title: mario_(sunshine)
body: An [[official alternate costume]] for [[Mario]] introduced in [[Super Mario Sunshine]], and later appeared in [[Super Mario Odyssey]] and [[Mario Kart Tour]]. Depicted wearing an [[open shirt|open]] [[blue shirt|blue]] [[collared shirt]] with [[short sleeves]] and a [[shine sprite]] print on it over his usual clothes barring sleeves. Also seen with a pair of [[blue-framed eyewear|blue-framed]] [[sunglasses]].

title: mario_(hakama)
body: An [[official alternate costume]] for [[Mario]] introduced in [[Super Mario Odyssey]] and later spread to [[Mario Kart Tour]]. Depicted wearing a [[black robe|black]] [[haori]] over a [[red shirt]] and [[grey hakama]], complete with [[tabi]], [[yellow footwear|yellow]] [[sandals]], and his usual [[white gloves]]. Notably, Mario doesn't wear a hat at all.

title: juna_unagi_(2nd_costume)
body:
The 2nd [[official alternate costume|costume]] of the [[indie virtual youtuber|Indie]] [[virtual youtuber|VTuber]] [[Juna Unagi]].

It consists of a [[halo]], a [[white shirt|white]] [[sleeveless shirt|sleeveless]] [[collared shirt]] with a [[cleavage cutout]], a [[short necktie|short]] [[yellow necktie]], [[white pants]], a [[white coat]], [[elbow gloves]], and [[white shoes|white]] [[high heels]].

For her [[official alternate hairstyle|official hairstyle]] in this costume, she has [[very long hair|very long]] [[brown hair]] tied into a [[ponytail]] with [[swept bangs]].

h4. Appearance

* !post #8755293: Reference sheet

title: mario_(golf)
body: An [[official alternate costume]] for [[Mario]] originally seen in [[NES Open Tournament Golf]] but reintroduced in [[Super Mario Odyssey]] and [[Mario Kart Tour]]. Depicted as wearing a [[striped headwear|striped]] [[red hat|red]] [[two-tone headwear|and]] [[white hat|white]] [[baseball cap]] with matching [[overalls]] over a [[blue shirt]] with [[long sleeves]] and a [[star print]], as well as his usual [[white gloves]] and [[brown footwear|brown]] [[shoes]]. Often seen holding a [[golf club]].

title: dr._mario
body: [[Mario]] as a [[doctor]]. He is the protagonist of the [[Dr. Mario (game)|]] series of games. Also appears in [[Super Smash Bros.]] and [[Mario Kart Tour]] as a playable character, as well as [[Super Mario Odyssey]] as a costume.

title: builder_mario
body:
An [[official alternate costume]] for [[Mario]] that first debuted in the [[Super Mario Maker]] games. Depicted wearing a [[red overalls|red version]] of his usual [[overalls]] and a [[yellow shirt]] instead of a red one, along with a [[brown belt]] complete with a [[brown bag|brown]] [[belt bag]] and a [[yellow hat|yellow]] [[hard hat]]. Often seen holding a [[hammer]].

Can also be unlocked as a costume in [[Super Mario Odyssey]], and obtained as a playable racer in [[Mario Kart Tour]].

title: leukocoria
body: Photograph phenomenon when the camera light flashes and reflects back into someone's eyes. Typically this creates a sort of white pupil but can also end up as a "double pupil" effect (i.e. the original pupil, then a white dot staggered overlay).

title: lyza_(made_in_abyss)
body:
Character From [[Made in Abyss]].

Lyza "[i]The Annihilator[/i]" is [[Riko_(made_in_abyss)|]]'s mother. Lyza is a legendary white whistle delver who accomplished many great discoveries about the secrets of the Abyss. She is known as the Lord of Annihilation for her tendency to exterminate all enemies she encountered within the Abyss, be it dangerous beasts or delvers from other countries.

In her canonical appearance, Lyza has a [[very long hair|very long]], [[wavy hair|wavy]] [[blonde hair]] with curls at the ends that reaches her knees, large [[blue eyes]], and a light skin-tone. Her attire consists of a [[red jacket]] and a [[brown helmet|brown]] [[helmet]].

h4. External links

* "Made in Abyss Wiki: Lyza":http://madeinabyss.wikia.com/wiki/Lyza

title: reg_(made_in_abyss)
body:
One of the main protagonists of [[Made in Abyss]]. He is voiced by [[Ise Mariya]].

A mysterious robot with the appearance of a young boy, he was discovered by [[riko_(made_in_abyss)|Riko]] in the Abyss. After becoming friends, he decided to protect her on her journey to the bottom of the Abyss. He has [[brown hair]], [[dark skin]], and [[pointy ears]]. Underneath his [[helmet]], he wears some kind of jagged, metal [[hairband]].

title: ozen
body:
[quote]For the Japanese term "ãŠè†³":[https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Tourists_dinner_in_Japan.jpg], use [[table]].
[/quote]
A character from [[Made in Abyss]].

Ozen "[i]The Immovable[/i]" is a legendary white whistle Delver who has made outstanding discoveries of The Abyss and retrieved numerous artifacts of incredible value. Even among her fellow white whistles, Ozen is renowned for her incredible physical strength. She is a mysterious entity, shrouded by countless rumors that are absurd but hard to refute. She lives at the Seeker Camp within the 2nd Layer of the Abyss, where she commands a small team of cave raiders known as "[i]The Layabouts.[/i]"

Ozen is a tall and rather slim woman, she has black [[short hair]] with white streaks. Often seen wearing a [[black coat]] and a [[black cape]]. When fully equipped for delving, she wears bulky [[black armor]] and a disc-shaped [[hat]] that covers her eyes.
Due to the [[Thousand-Men pin]]s embedded in her body she is usually depicted with [[gradient skin]] and/or [[colored extremities]] when [[nude]] or [[partially undressed]].

h4. See also

* "Made in Abyss Wiki: Ozen":http://madeinabyss.wikia.com/wiki/Ozen

title: yuriko_omega
body: A character (as well as ingame unit) from [[Command & Conquer: Red Alert 3|Red Alert 3]], a homage (or parody) of Japanese magic girls (and psychic characters). Arguably the most powerful commando unit in the game. Her real name is Matsui Yuriko, revealed in her campaign in the Uprising Expansion pack which shows that she was kidnapped by the Japanese government at a very young age to mould those with psychic talents into weapons for the Empire.

title: jr_205_series

title: zako_(phrase)
body:
[i]Zaa~ko[/i] is a phrase which originates from [[Yuzu-Soft]]'s game [[Tenshi Souzou Re-boot!]]. One of the main heroines, [[Tanikaze Amane]] teases her brother, a former demon lord who lost his power, by calling him a zako. It can be translated as a "small fry" or "prey", something really small and weak, like level 1 monsters. "Loser" is a close English equivalent. 

h4. See also

* [[mesugaki]]

title: groudon
body:
A Ground-type Legendary [[pokemon (creature)|PokÃ©mon]], #0383 in the National PokÃ©dex.

A [[dinosaur]]-like creature with a red and grey body covered in [[spikes]]. Has [[claws]], [[sharp teeth]], and [[yellow eyes]] with [[black sclera]]e.

Sought after by [[Team Magma]] due to its ability to expand the continents. The mascot of [[pokemon rse|PokÃ©mon Ruby]] and [[pokemon oras|Omega Ruby]]; its counterpart is [[Kyogre]], which it often feuds with. These feuds can only be quelled by [[Rayquaza]].

The [[Red Orb (pokemon)|]] allows it to transform into [[Primal Groudon]].

title: scottish_flag
body: More properly known as St. Andrew's Saltire, St. Andrew being the patron saint of [[Scotland]], who was crucified on a [[saltire]] (X-shaped cross) rather than conventional cross. It consists of a white saltire centered on a blue field. The [[English Flag]], Scottish Flag and St. Patrick's Saltire are combined to form the [[Union Jack]], the flag of the United Kingdom.

title: kamen_rider_virgo_(game)
body:
A work of [[Kamen Rider]] fanfiction that was developed into a RPG scenario using "SRC (Simulation RPG Construction)":[http://ja.wikipedia.org/wiki/Simulation_RPG_Construction], Windows freeware created by Kei that allows user to create strategy role-playing games, by "Kishimoto Miyuki":[http://twitter.com/miyukivirgo]. Not to be confused with [[virgo zodiarts|an antagonist]] in [[Kamen Rider Fourze (series)|]].

Despite being a beta version, it was highly praised for its setting that combined the so-called Shouwa Rider and Heisei Rider settings, and its excellent production and plot. However, due to the excessive time it took for development, the scenario rapidly spun out of control as the number of heroes appearing increased leading to total chaos, and the project died out naturally before its completion when Kishimoto made his professional debut as "a scenario writer":[http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/encyclopedia/people.php?id=77288]. Former fans of this game believe that Virgo lives on in the TV series supervised by Kishimoto such as [[Ben-Tou]] and [[Tales of the Abyss]] to console themselves. 

The main character of the story, Honjou Maki was one of 12 altered humans created by the evil organization ERASER, each named for one of the 12 [[zodiac]] signs, and after escaping from the organization, battled evil as "Kamen Rider Virgo" (a female Kamen Rider). The secondary protagonist, Shigure Kyousuke was the hero of the sister series "SRC Hero Club," who transforms into "Kamen Rider Otis." 

h4. External links

* [[niconico|NicoVideo]]: "Kamen Rider Virgo Opening":[http://www.nicovideo.jp/watch/sm3689088]

title: remove_before_flight_tag
body: The â€œRemove Before Flightâ€ [[tag]] is an integral safety sign for aircraft maintenance and notifies aircraft personnel that its attached component needs removal before use. The tags are checked during ground handling processes, usually as part of a standardized checklist. Failure to remove the tag and its attachment can result in terrible consequences ranging from a simple part failure to a complete aircraft shutdown.

title: yunru_(mental_omega)
body: The hero unit for the Chinese Subfaction of the Soviet Union in the [[Mental Omega (mod)|]] mod for [[Command & Conquer: Red Alert 2|Command & Conquer: Red Alert 2: Yuri's Revenge]] and the founder of the Foehn Revolt. Originally a teenage prodigy pressured into helping to advance the People's Republic of China's weapons programs with her skill at computer engineering, robotics, and seismology, when she realised the true nature of the threat Yuri's Epsilon posed, she eventually broke with the Chinese government when it was too set on trying to usurp the Soviet Union from Russia to focus on the real threat, making her way to Alaska with a growing crew of followers to found a new army. Yunru is generally a support unit, being able to disable multiple vehicles in an area at long range with her cybernetic warfare suite, though if brought into a base she can use her earthquake generator to level a huge chunk of it all at once.

title: totenkopf
body:
German word for "dead man's head" ([[skull]]).

An [[insignia]] used by elite German units since the 18th century. Initially used by the cavalry. Commonly associated with the [[Nazi|Totenkopf-SS]], who used it as their [[SS insignia|emblem]] in [[World War II]]. It was also used by the armored corps and the tank crews of the [[Wehrmacht]] (who are often confused as [[Waffen-SS]] because of this and their black [[military uniform|uniforms]]). The most well-known form (the "3rd SS Panzer Division Totenkopf":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/3rd_SS_Panzer_Division_Totenkopf]) is a skull at 3/4 view overlaid on two crossed bones, however the [[insignia]] may lack the mandible or the crossbones and remain a totenkopf.

title: ghoul_(mobile_suit)
body:
A fictional manned giant robot from the [[Gundam]] [[mecha]]verse. It appears in the Mobile Suit [[Gundam Blazing Shadow]] light novel series.

[b]YMS-23C Ghoul[/b]

A [[close-quarters combat|CQC]] prototype [[mobile suit]] that takes inspiration from Zimmad MS designs. It was developed through illegal means by the Hell's Gate [[Zeon]] remnants. 

It is fitted with a specialized cockpit and maneuvering system developed by Hell's Gate that requires the pilot to undergo inhumane body modifications in order to use it. 

Unlike most Zeon mobile suits, the Ghoul features magnetic coating, resulting in high reaction speed. These features allow an amateur pilot to fight evenly against experienced soldiers.

title: close-quarters_combat
body:
[b]CQC[/b] ([b]Close-Quarters Combat[/b]) is a system of combined combat techniques which allow rapid alternation between armed and hand-to-hand combat while engaging enemy personnel. 

In the typical CQC stance, the user holds their [[gun]] (a one handed weapon such as a [[handgun]]) with their dominant hand while supporting it with the other hand, which holds their CQC [[knife]]. By using this stance, the gun remains steady for accurate engagement of opponents outside the range of unarmed combat, while allowing a quick transition to the knife for close-work. 

In the [[metal gear solid|Metal Gear Solid universe]] it's a style of close combat techniques developed together by [[The Boss]] and [[Big Boss]] of [[Metal Gear Solid 3: Snake Eater]]. 


Use this tag for when a character in the picture is wielding a gun and a knife.

h4. See also

* [[Dual wielding]]

title: command_&_conquer:_red_alert_3
body:
The third main entry (i.e. not counting expansion packs) in the [[Command & Conquer]] Red Alert series.

Plot: The Soviets, who were losing WWIII, used their experimental time machine to travel back in time to remove Einstein from the time stream. They succeed, but in doing so merely made the situation more complex by giving into existence the Empire of the Rising Sun. Thus in this new timeline three factions (Allies, Soviets, and Empire) wages war for the dominance of the world.

Gameplay: continuing the trend of the previous game of the series in more cartoony aesthetics while the gameplay shifted away from macromanaging of resources & production to that of micromanaging special abilities of individual units, of which every single unit has a secondary ability of some kind.

Other: notable for a lot of celebrity actors and actresses appearing in the FMV cutscenes.

title: command_&_conquer:_generals
body:
A real-time strategy video game developed by [[electronic arts|EA Pacific]] and released in February 2003. 

It is set in the near future, relative to the game's release date, using technology that is either existent, in development, or theorized. The game features a conflict between the [[Global Liberation Army]] (GLA), an organization resembling a [[terrorist]] group, and the superpowers of the [[China|Peopleâ€™s Republic of China]] (China) and the [[united states|United States of America]] (USA). 

The game operates in a similar manner to other titles in the [[Command & Conquer]] series, where players construct bases, train units, acquire resources on one of the game's maps to fund their operations, and then defeat their opponents by eliminating their bases and armies. It is the first Command & Conquer RTS game to use 3D graphics in-game. The game takes place in an entirely separate continuity that is completely unrelated to the [[command & conquer: red alert 2|Red Alert]] universe or the [[Command & Conquer: Tiberian Sun|Tiberium]] universe.

An expansion pack titled [i]"Command & Conquer: Generals â€“ Zero Hour":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Command_&_Conquer:_Generals_%E2%80%93_Zero_Hour][/i] was released in September 2003, adding several new abilities and units to each side, and a new mode of play called Generals' Challenge, along with a lot more changes, new features and bug/glitch fixes.

The series has received controversy from media watchdogs due to its national stereotyping and the ability to play as a terrorist-like organization, particularly during the height of the "War on Terror":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/War_on_terror. Longtime Command & Conquer fans also objected to the association of their franchise with a game that resembled other real-time strategy games more than traditional Command & Conquer gameplay. 

Despite this, the game received positive reviews from fans and critics for its solid and action-packed gameplay, as well as receiving praise for the humorous and memorable voicelines for many of its units. It has since gained a cult following, with fans of the series continuing to develop mods that change the gameplay significantly.


h4. See Also

* [[Command & Conquer]]

title: global_defense_initiative
body:
The Global Defense Initiate (GDI) is a faction in the [[Command & Conquer]] Tiberium series.  

Formed by the UN as a special task force to deal with significant threats to world peace, they later become the government of humanity (barring the parts under Nod's control) after the spread of the toxic self-replicating substance named Tiberium devastates much of the planet.

Curiously for a "good guy" faction, their military doctrine relies on strong overwhelming force and firepower.

title: hildolfr
body:
A fictional manned giant combat robot from the [[Gundam]] [[mecha]]verse. It appears in [[Gundam MS IGLOO]].

[b]YMT-05 Hildolfr [/b]

A monstrous "[[mobile_suit|mobile]] [[tank]]" built by [[Zeon]] with the intent of busting fortresses and defeating land battleships while retaining excellent speed. 

It could partially transform into "Mobile Mode" - when in this form, its torso would raise from the chassis, revealing two manipulators capable of wielding weapons and being able to pivot its huge main gun - however, said gun was so powerful, firing it while the Hildolfr was not held in place by braces risked tipping the machine over with every shot due to the massive recoil.

title: command_&_conquer
body:
[b]Command & Conquer[/b] (C&C) is a series primarily of real time strategy PC [[video game]]s that began with the eponymous first title in 1995.  First created by Westwood Studios, and later by [[Electronic Arts]] after they acquired Westwood and later dissolved Westwood Studios in 2003.  

Many former Westwood staff founded the studio Petroglyph Games, which was tapped by EA to develop a remaster of the original C&C games that was released in 2020.  Along with Westwood's previous RTS game Dune 2 (based on the sci-fi series [[Dune (series)|]]), the early C&C games helped codified the RTS genre.  The games were well know for their large tanks, live action cutscenes, mostly solid (albeit cheesy) story in the earlier installments, and great music.

The three C&C sub series:

* [i]Tiberium[/i] series (C&C Tiberian Dawn, [[Command & Conquer: Tiberian Sun]], [[Command & Conquer: Tiberium Wars]], C&C4 Tiberium Twilight): A toxic green alien space substance crashes on Earth.  Initially a boon by leeching out important minerals from the ground, making mining and energy easier to come by, it starts replicating out of control and mutating the landscape. Two initial factions, the UN agency the [[Global Defense Initiative]] and the mysterious cult the [[Brotherhood of Nod]], end up fighting over control of the world.

* [i]Red Alert[/i] series ([[Command & Conquer: Red Alert]], [[command & conquer: red alert 2|RA2]], [[command & conquer: red alert 3|RA3]]):  After World War II, [[Albert Einstein]] creates a time machine and goes back in time to erase [[Adolf Hitler]] from the timeline.  This ends up causing a timeline with a stronger Soviet Union that invades Europe.  The two initial factions were the Allies and the Soviet Union.  They're later joined by the third faction, The Empire of the Rising Sun.  The series generally has a much campier tone and comic book style plot.  Time travel plays a role throughout the various games.

* [i][[command & conquer: generals|Generals]][/i] series: the War of Terror in RTS format! The only series completely made by EALA and lacking live action cutscenes (except Generals Zero Hour).  The series featured three factions: United States, China, and the terrorist group, the Global Liberation Army.

In 2025, the Source codes for Generals (and Zero Hour), Red Alert 3, and Tiberium Wars were released, making their engines test to a new generation of future modifications. There won't be source codes for Red Alert 2 and Tiberian Sun at the moment.

title: command_&_conquer:_tiberian_sun
body:
[b]Command & Conquer: Tiberian Sun[/b] is a 1999 real-time strategy [[video game]] developed by Westwood Studios, published by [[Electronic Arts]], and released exclusively for Microsoft Windows on August 27, 1999. 

The game is the sequel to the 1995 game [[Command & Conquer]]. It featured new semi-3D graphics, a more futuristic [[science fiction]] setting, and new gameplay features such as vehicles capable of hovering or burrowing. 

The main story of the game focuses on a second war between the UN-backed [[Global Defense Initiative]] (GDI) and the cult-like [[Brotherhood of Nod]], both seeking to rule over an [[earth_(planet)|Earth]] which is undergoing rapid ecological collapse.

Tiberian Sun was one of the most anticipated games of 1999. Its development suffered numerous delays, with several features being cut before release. However, it was a commercial success and received positive reviews from critics, despite some of the technical bugs in the game. The dark atmosphere, foreboding soundtrack, and slow paced gameplay of Tiberian Sun received a mixed reception from fans upon release, although have earned it a cult following since. Its story of a military-industrial complex preoccupied with [[terrorism]] rather than environmental failure has been hailed as a metaphor for modern times. 

Several additional features were added to the game with the Firestorm expansion pack, including new units and a multiplayer global war mode. The game was later succeeded by the 2007 sequel [[command & conquer: tiberium wars|Command & Conquer 3: Tiberium Wars]], and was later licensed by Electronic Arts as freeware on February 12, 2010.

title: command_&_conquer:_tiberium_wars
body:
[b][i]Command & Conquer 3: Tiberium Wars[/i][/b] is a 2007 [[science fiction]] real-time strategy [[video game]] developed and published by [[Electronic Arts]] for [[Microsoft Windows]], [[Mac OS X]] and [[Xbox 360]] platforms, and released internationally in March 2007.

The game is a direct sequel to the 1999 game [[Command & Conquer: Tiberian Sun]], and takes place roughly seventeen years after the game's expansion pack Firestorm, in which Tiberium has grown to become a considerable threat to the planet, leading to the world's political borders and territories being remade into zones denoting the level of contamination by the alien substance. 

The game's story sees the [[Global Defense Initiative]] and the [[Brotherhood of Nod]] engage in a new global conflict, this time as major superpowers, only for the war to attract the attention of a new extraterrestrial faction known as the Scrin, which attacks both sides while harvesting Tiberium for its own purpose.

The game brought about several changes in gameplay, some introduced in [[Command & Conquer: Red Alert 2]], including garrisonable structures, neutral tech buildings, unit upgrades and veteran levels, and special powers unique for each playable faction. Other modes include a skirmish battle mode and multiplayer games.

The game received favorable reviews, and proved a commercial success following its launch, with a stand-alone expansion pack released a year later on March 24, 2008, titled Command & Conquer 3: Kane's Wrath.

title: global_liberation_army
body:
One of the three main factions that are playable in [[Command & Conquer: Generals]]. 

A violent movement and rogue state that serves as the main antagonist in the games' campaign. It is made up of various terrorist groups, revolutionaries, criminal organizations, and other movements opposed to imperialism, united under one banner. The GLAâ€™s stated goal is to oppose the imperialism practiced by the [[united states|United States of America]] and the [[china|Peopleâ€™s Republic of China]], and under the pretense of liberation, it seeks to dominate the world.

Due to its technological disadvantages compared to the two other factions, the GLA has comparatively weak ground vehicles and no air force, prompting it to use guerrilla tactics such as tunneling, suicide bombing, hijacking, and ambushes. 

The faction has gained notoriety and controversy for its parallels to Al-Qaeda, especially during the height of the War on Terror.

title: terrorist_(c&c:_generals)
body:
A unit in [[Command & Conquer: Generals]] that is known for its cost-effectiveness and ability to cause significant damage to enemy troops by detonating the [[explosive]] [[vest]] they wear, taking enemies along with them in a [[suicide]] attack. 

Due to censorship, the Terrorist was removed from the [[germany|German]] version of both Generals and Zero Hour and replaced by a [[bomb]] on wheels. Other than the visuals, however, the functionality is exactly the same. This version became very popular with the game's modding community. The Terrorist can also hijack civilian vehicles to move faster, turning them into weaponized [[car]]s.


h4. See Also

* [[Global Liberation Army]]

They can be small enough for one person to use (like the [[starfighter]]s) or as big as planets.

title: last_bastion
body: A subfaction of the Foehn Revolt in the Mental Omega mod for Command & Conquer Red Alert 2: Yuri's Revenge based in the Revolt's central headquarters in Alaska that exaggerates the general qualities of the Foehn Revolt, being an incredibly slow but very tanky faction that seeks to be the "immovable object" that will roll towards its opponents' doom with a gradual but implacable advance. Heavily emphasises Nanotechnology and Plasma Railguns.

title: teratorn
body: The basic anti-air vehicle of all subfactions of the Foehn Revolt in the Mental Omega Mod for Command & Conquer Red Alert 2: Yuri's Revenge. A wholly robotic unmanned armoured vehicle that first locks onto aircraft before releasing powerful golden missiles against them that will pursue a target relentlessly until impact. While only able to attack air units, unlike the Soviet Half-Track, Epsilon Gatling Tank, and Allied IFVs, the Teratorn is immune to mind control and is more efficient at AA as a result.

title: railgun_tower
body: The advanced anti-vehicle base defence of all subfactions of the Foehn Revolt in the Mental Omega mod for Command & Conquer Red Alert 2: Yuri's Revenge. Unlike its counterparts in other factions, the Inferno Tower, the Tesla Coil, and the Prism Tower, it is only cost-efficient against vehicles, not infantry, but it is both cheaper and fires faster than its counterparts, reducing enemy armoured columns to scrap with its plasma railgun.

title: plasmerizer
body: The Super-Base defence turret for the Last Bastion subfaction of the Foehn Revolt in the Mental Omega Mod for Command & Conquer Red Alert 2: Yuri's Revenge. Outranging all units save for naval siege units, the Plasmerizer is huge, takes up significant amounts of base power, and very durable to allow it to charge up a massive plasma railgun blast that deals considerable splash damage against all ground targets, with vehicles getting hit the hardest. So long as the Plasmerizer is screened against faster moving units and aircraft, the fact that the player can only have one of them at a time is of little consequence as they should only ever need one.

title: double_dildo
body: A [[dildo]] where both ends are shaped to be used for penetration (either [[double penetration]] or [[shared object insertion]]).

title: mastodon_tank
body: The superheavy monster tank of the Last Bastion Subfaction of the Foehn Revolt in the Mental Omega Mod for Command & Conquer Red Alert 2: Yuri's Revenge. An enormous vehicle (the largest mass producible ground unit in the entire game by voxel size) with an equally huge health pool and very little speed, the Mastodon is armed with a plasma railgun that takes time to charge up and fire but hits with a formidable amount of anti-vehicle splash damage. The Mastodon also can very rapidly recover its health so long as it remains still, and outranges most non-artillery units, but has relatively weak alpha strike damage due to its emphasis on cleaning out hordes of vehicles and simply outlasting other vehicles in its weight class.

title: knightframe
body: The basic infantry unit of all Foehn Revolt subfactions in the Mental Omega mod for Command & Conquer Red Alert 2: Yuri's Revenge. The most expensive, durable, and hardest hitting basic infantry unit of the four factions and the only one with innate splash damage and the ability to hit air units, the Knightframe is a heavily armoured soldier in an exoskeletal frame carrying a "very heavy machine gun" good against light vehicles, infantry, and softer aircraft.

title: giantsbane
body: A type of infantry unit for the Last Bastion subfaction for the Foehn Revolt in the Mental Omega Mod for Command & Conquer Red Alert 2: Yuri's Revenge. The Giantsbane is a power armour equipped cyborg infantry unit outfitted for heavy-duty long-range anti-air and anti-vehicle capabilities, that can strike from considerable distance with its guided golden rocket launchers, with a monstrous health pool and equally monstrously slow speed that while not able to directly damage infantry can paralyse them from a great distance.

title: foehn_revolt_symbol
body: The symbol of the Foehn Revolt Faction in the Mental Omega mod for Command & Conquer Red Alert 2: Yuri's Revenge. Takes the shape of a heavily stylised curved shark symbol pointing rightwards.

title: foehn_revolt
body: A new, original faction created for the Mental Omega mod of Command & Conquer Red Alert 2: Yuri's Revenge born of the Chinese Heroine Yunru's alliance with other Soviet and Allied remnants as well as some of the defectors from Epsilon's Scorpion Cell; particularly Rashidi. The Foehn Revolt emphasises a quality over quantity playstyle and victory through adaptability and endurance over trickery, raw power, or speed.

title: bison_tank
body: A type of tank used by the Last Bastion subfaction of the Foehn Revolt in the Mental Omega mod for Command & Conquer Red Alert 2: Yuri's Revenge, capable of using nanites to rapidly self-repair if damaged as long as it remains still to emphasise a defensive playstyle.

title: condor_gunship
body: A type of aircraft used by the Last Bastion Subfaction of the Foehn Revolt in the Mental Omega mod for Command & Conquer Red Alert 2: Yuri's Revenge, a sturdier and more heavily armed counterpart to the Buzzard available to the other two subfactions that trades out the ability to drop stun mines for an extra cannon good against buildings and some speed for greater durability.

title: holy_grail_(warhammer)
body: The Holy Grail, also known as the Grail of Life, the White Grail or simply the Grail, is the enchanted chalice kept by the Lady of the Lake, the chief deity of [[Bretonnia]], that is not like any other religious relic or magical item. It cannot be taken from her or kept by any mortal person and serves as the most revered symbol of her sacred blessings over the land. Any mortal Questing Knight who drinks from the Grail's magical waters will thereafter be transformed into one of the Lady's Grail Knights, the living saints of Bretonnia.

title: bretonnia
body:
Bretonnia, formally the Kingdom of Bretonnia, also known more prosaically as the "Land of Chivalry," is a highly martial Human feudal kingdom of the Old World that lies between the lands of the Grey Mountains and the Great Ocean. Bretonnia is second only in size to that of the [[Empire_(Warhammer Fantasy)|]] among the realms of Men in the Old World, and is both the Empire's chief rival and closest ally, having a culture and society that revolves around the ideals of nobility, a strict social hierarchy based on aristocratic birthright, and the upholding of a strictly enforced code of chivalry.

https://warhammerfantasy.fandom.com/wiki/Bretonnia

title: dhl
body:
DHL International "GmbH":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gesellschaft_mit_beschr%C3%A4nkter_Haftung] is an American-founded German courier, parcel, and express mail service which is a division of the German logistics company Deutsche Post DHL. Deutsche Post DHL is the world's largest logistics company, operating in over 220 countries and territories worldwide. The company delivers over 1.3 billion parcels per year.

DHL is an acronym of the last names of the company's original founders: Adrian [b]D[/b]alsey, Larry [b]H[/b]illblom, and Robert [b]L[/b]ynn

title: cancer_death_mask
body:
[[Gold Saint]] of the Cancer constellation in the original [[Saint Seiya]] anime and manga series.

A treacherous, unscrupulous and cowardly Saint. He sides with the evil Pope during the battle of Sanctuary despite knowing he wished to kill and usurp [[athena_(saint_seiya)|Athena]]. He believes it's only logical that he sides with whoever provides him with the most benefits.

His real name is unknown; Deathmask is a nickname he received from his peers due to the way he adorns the Cancer Temple with the faces of his many victims, children included. In the English localisation,  his name was changed to Cancer Mephisto.

In the original manga, he has [[short_hair|short]] [[grey hair]] and [[red eyes]]. His anime design gives him [[purple hair|violet hair]] and   [[purple eyes|eyes]].

title: lynette_bishop
body:
Lynette Bishop is a character from [[Strike Witches]]. She has [[blue eyes]] and light [[brown hair]], worn in a [[single braid]]. Her uniform is a jacket over a [[sweater vest]]. Her familiar is a Scottish Fold cat. She also has a sister, [[Wilma Bishop]].

Her pilot archetype is unclear, but is likely one of the children of famed Canadian WWI pilot "Billy Bishop":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Billy_Bishop, who is the pilot archetype for Minnie Bishop, Lynette's mother. Lynette also has an older sister, Wilma, who is also a Witch, and likely based on Billy Bishop's son, Arthur. Although based on a Canadian, Lynette is officially said to be from Brittania.

h4. Equipment

* [[boys anti tank rifle|Mk. I Boys Anti-tank Rifle]]
* [[machine gun|Bren light machine gun]]

title: frame_break
body:
A visual technique where an element (such as a character, object, effect, or text bubble) within a comic panel, illustration, or other framed artwork extends beyond its defined border or frame. This creates the illusion that the element is breaking free from the two-dimensional confines of the art, often appearing to "pop out" towards the viewer or flow into adjacent visual spaces.

title: death_jail_summer_escape
body:
[b]Raiding Chariot Dungeon: Celtic Prison[br]Death Jail Summer Escape ~Medb's Prison of Sin and Despair 2017~[/b]
[quote]While each team races through the scorching heat at full throttle, everyone tumbles into a deep ravine just as they're about to cross the finish line.
Master and Mash hurry to investigate and see if the competitors are okay, and learn that all the participants have been thrown in jail!
Can the incarcerated Servants find a way to escape the supposedly inescapable prison?[/quote]

title: dead_heat_summer_race!
body:
[b]Summer Racing Festival: Ishtar Cup[br]Dead Heat Summer Race! ~The Ishtar Cup of Hopes and Dreams 2017~[/b]
[quote]While Master enjoys a well-deserved break with Mash,
Ishtar shows up with a big, too-happy smile.
She informs the pair that she found a new Singularity,
and warns that the world will be in danger if something isn't done.

After stopping Mash from requesting an official Order,
Ishtar mentions a certain ritual of her devising to eliminate the Singularity.
A summer festival to get everyone all fired up will be just the thing to deal with this Singularity...

That's right...the only option is to hold a cross country race![/quote]

title: personification
body:
When objects or non-humanoid characters ([[animal]]s, [[creature]]s, [[non-humanoid robot]]s etc.) are transformed into humans or humanoids.

Use [[humanization]] instead if a humanoid character ([[humanoid robot]]s, [[furry|furries]] etc.) is turned into a human.

[b]Do not use this tag on copyrights revolving around personifications[/b], unless the image explicitly shows them as a personification (such as [[creature and personification]] posts). This includes [[Kantai Collection]], [[Azur Lane]], [[Warship Girls R]], [[Umamusume]], [[Touken Ranbu]], [[Girls' Frontline]], [[Axis Powers Hetalia]], and others (see: topic #10067).

body:
Hannibal Barca (ãƒãƒ³ãƒ‹ãƒãƒ«ãƒ»ãƒãƒ«ã‚«, Hannibaru Baruka?), Class Name unknown, is an unknown class Servant summoned "After" the Holy Grail Warâ€â€ in [[Fate/Requiem]]. 

Hannibal is a muscular middle-aged man with copper skin, a lush beard, and stout, hairy arms. He is dressed in traditional battle garments and has a sheathed blade at his belt.

Outside of combat Hannibal seems like a completely different person. In his casual clothes he is dressed as if he were at a resort, in a short-sleeved safari shirt and shorts. He has round-framed glasses that give off an intellectual air, contrasting the rest of his outfit.

title: vise_(tool)
body:
A [b]vise[/b] (or vice in British English) is a mechanical apparatus used to physically secure an object in place, to allow work to be performed on it, without it moving in different positions or away from the person or machine that processing the work-piece into an useful or finished product. Vises have two parallel jaws, one fixed and the other movable, threaded in and out by a screw and lever.

title: boss_(saints_row)
body:
The Protagonist (later known as the Boss) is the player character in [[Saints Row]], [[Saints Row 2]], [[Saints Row: The Third]] and [[Saints Row IV]]. The Saints Row series largely concerns The Protagonist's adventures as a 3rd Street Saints gang member, starting as a nobody initiated into the gang, second-in-command, and finally leader. Throughout this journey, The Protagonist takes the 3rd Street Saints from a small-time gang from the Row to a "household brand name" in Stilwater and then Steelport. During the events of Saints Row IV, The Protagonist becomes President of the United States.

The Protagonist lacks a definitive physical appearance, as The Protagonist's appearance can be changed using the Image As Designed plastic surgeon. In Saints Row 2 onwards, The Protagonist's gender can be changed, thus retconning The Protagonist's established gender as a male

The Protagonist does not have a given name throughout the series, and has been referred to as playa, son, and Boss throughout the games. [[Kinzie Kensington]] knows their real name, but is stopped mid-sentence before saying it, as The Protagonist warns her that somebody else might be listening in on their radio conversation. On television they're given various titles, including "Leader of the Saints" and "Local Psychopath". In Saints Row IV, they are referred to as "The President of the United States" or simply "The President".

If the "[[Nolan North]]" voice is selected in Saints Row IV during the mission A Pleasant Day, Kinzie asks The Protagonist to be themselves while causing destruction, and he replies "be... Nolan?". While in gameplay, the voice randomly says "that is how Nolan rolls".

title: american_mcgee's_alice
body:
American McGee's Alice is a third-person action PC video game which takes place in the Alice's Adventures in Wonderland universe. This Alice is designed by [[American McGee (artist)|]].

Set years after [[Alice's Adventures in Wonderland]] and [i]Through the Looking-Glass and What Alice Found There[/i], the game features a more mature, cynical and macabre incarnation of Alice.

She is now an older, dark-brown haired young woman with emerald green eyes. She wears a dark navy dress and a white apron with alchemical symbols, and is often drawn with a long butcher [[knife]].

The game is titled "Alice in Nightmare" (ã‚¢ãƒªã‚¹ ã‚¤ãƒ³ ãƒŠã‚¤ãƒˆãƒ¡ã‚¢) in Japan.

The game also has a sequel titled [[Alice: Madness Returns]].

A prequel titled [i]Alice: Asylum[/i] was pitched, but failed to be greenlit. Following this, McGee chose to permanently retire the series and step away from game development.

h4. External links

* "Wikipedia: American McGee's Alice":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/American_McGee's_Alice

title: akashi_kuniyuki
body:
Male personification of the sword Tsurikane Kiri. Tachi-class sword. 

In real life, the sword was smithed by Rai Kuniyuki, who founded the Rai school of swords. Over the years the sword was handed down through the Matsudaira Clan in the Akashi region of Japan. Currently stored in the Society for the Preservation of Japanese Art Swords in Tokyo. 

In [i][[Touken Ranbu]][/i], Akashi considers himself the guardian of [[Hotarumaru]] and [[Aizen Kunitoshi]]. He has a lackadaisical personality and makes a big deal over not wanting to work or be motivated. However, he mentions that he will get involved if Hotarumaru is involved, showing rather blatant favoritism towards Hotarumaru over Aizen. His being a parental figure to the two swords is due to the fact that Kuniyuki's master is the father of Rai Kunitoshi, who smithed Aizen and Hotarumaru later on in life. The boy is also a bit of a space-case in game as well.


Has [[black hair]] with two red [[hairclip|hairclips]], [[green eyes]], and [[glasses]]. His default shirt is [[untucked_shirt|halfway tucked in]], and wears [[half gloves]] with a black [[open_jacket|jacket]] and black [[knee boots]].

Voiced by [[Asari Ryouta]]. Character designer is [[Futaba Hazuki]].

title: fire_emblem:_shadow_dragon_and_the_blade_of_light
body:
The very first [[Fire Emblem]] game, released for the Nintendo Entertainment System only in Japan in 1990. 
It wouldn't be until 2020 that an English translated version was released for the [[ Nintendo Switch]] as part of the series' 30th anniversary. 
It was also fully remade as [[Fire Emblem: Shadow Dragon]] for the Nintendo DS in 2008.

This game introduces the protagonist [[Marth (fire emblem)|]], whom Western players were first introduced to in [[Super Smash Bros.|Super Smash Bros. Melee]] before the actual game starring him was released.

title: coquelic_(path_to_nowhere)
body:
A playable character from [[Path to Nowhere]], her name derives from the word 'Coquelicot', a name for wild corn poppy flowers and a shade of red. Voiced by [[Ichimichi Mao]] (as MÂ·AÂ·O).

An S rank Sinner, Mentor of the assassin organisation Garden, she is often associated and/or seen with [[red flower|red]] [[poppy (flower)|]] flowers, and always seen [[smile|smiling]]. Her alignment is Limbo.

A woman with [[very long hair|very long]] [[white hair]] and [[red eyes]], wears a large red [[hair flower]] ornament, [[ribbon earrings]] and white [[teardrop facial mark]] makeups.

She is seen only in underwear consisting of [[white nightgown]] [[lingerie]] ([[babydoll]]), [[detached sleeves|detached]] [[white sleeves]], [[white shrug]] and [[white panties]], the nightgown itself has [[burnt clothes|burn marks]]. She is seen using a [[huge weapon|huge]] narrow bladed [[sword]].

title: borg
body:
A fictional alien race from the [i][[Star Trek]][/i] franchise.
They are a cybernetic race ruthlessly devoted to attaining perfection by, converting, or "assimilating" other races into the Borg Collective.
A single Borg is distinguished by sickly skin, and many robotic implants, most notably a single prosthetic eye. Their ships are usually cube-shaped, and all crew of a ship speak in one voice.

title: watanabe_poemi
body: The main character of [[Puni Puni Poemi]], Watanabe Poemi is an insanely hyperactive girl with dreams of being a seiyuu. Ironically, she's voiced by [[Kobayashi Yumiko]], who is already a famous seiyuu. This joke is further added by Poemi always calling herself 'Kobayashi'. She is the daughter of [[Nabeshin]] and Kumi-Kumi in an alternate universe to [[Excel Saga]]. With the powers of a magical dead fish (no, I'm not making that up), Poemi can transform into [[Puni Puni Poemi (character)|Puni Puni Poemi]] to protect the Earth from an alien invasion.

He is known for his flamboyant and positive demeanor and usually responds to the greeting "How are you?" with an upbeat "I'm super! Thanks for asking!"

title: manuel_noriega
body:
Manuel Antonio Noriega Moreno (February 11, 1934 - May 29, 2017) was a [[panama|Panamanian]] dictator (from 1983 to 1989) and military officer, as well as a former intelligence source for the [[CIA]]. 
His violent leadership and growing involvement in drug-trafficking and money laundering eventually led the [[united_states|American]] goverment to launch an invasion on Panama in 1989 with the objective of capturing him.

title: mr._slave
body: Character from [[South Park]], Mr. Slave is the husband of [[Big Gay Al]] and the ex-boyfriend of Herbert Garrison. He first appears in the Season Five episode "Butters' Very Own Episode", although he is only heard. He is then seen physically in "The Death Camp of Tolerance".

title: themis_legal_academy_school_uniform
body:
A [[school uniform]] worn by students of Themis Legal Academy in [[Ace Attorney]]. First introduced in [[Ace Attorney Investigations 2: Prosecutor's Gambit]], and later used in [[Phoenix Wright: Ace Attorney - Dual Destinies]].

The uniform depends on their gender which course a given student is taking - either studying to become a judge, prosecutor, or a defense attorney.

Boys' uniform always has the same basic shape, with the only change being the color:
* Defense course students wear a [[blue jacket|blue]] [[collared jacket|collared]] [[jacket]] with the [[school emblem]] and [[long sleeves]] with [[double horizontal stripe]]s, [[blue pants|blue]] [[pants]], and [[black shoes|black]] [[loafers]].
* Prosecutor course students wear a [[red jacket]] and [[red pants]].
* Judge course students wear a [[black jacket]] and [[black pants]].

Girls' uniform is split even further:
* Defense course students wear [[serafuku]]s consisting of a [[white shirt|white]] [[short sleeves|short-sleeved]] [[sailor shirt|sailor]] [[shirt]] with a [[blue sailor collar]] and the [[school emblem]]; a [[yellow neckerchief|yellow]] [[neckerchief]], a [[blue skirt|blue]] [[pleated skirt|pleated]] [[miniskirt]], and [[black shoes|black]] [[loafers]].
* Prosecutor course students wear the same outfit as defense course students, except the [[red sailor collar|sailor collar]] and [[red skirt|skirt]] are red.
* Judge course students wear a [[short dress|short]] [[black dress|black]] [[ribbed dress|ribbed]] [[dress]] with a [[wing collar]], the [[school emblem]] and [[long sleeves|long]] [[juliet sleeves]] with [[sleeve cuffs|cuffs]] with [[buttons]]; a [[yellow neckerchief|yellow]] [[neckerchief]], and [[black shoes|black]] [[loafers]].

title: bad_gun_anatomy
body:
Tag given to an image featuring a [[gun|firearm]] that is drawn such that it is: impossible to be used reasonably (ex: the stock is so long that it prohibits shouldering, lacking a trigger or means to fire, etc), absurd (ex: non-deliberate barrel curvature, abnormally large/small bore or barrel OD for the chambering and vice-versa, barrel/bolt coming out of an optic, etc), resembles a caricature of the firearm it is supposed to be, has overbearing errors (ex: whole cartridges being ejected or shot out, single action firearm going 'click click click', etc ), or just generally looks trash.

This tag should not be used to describe depictions of operator error such as backwards magazines or optics. It should also not be used to describe firearms that have small faults in furniture or continuity (ex: grip slightly too long or at slightly wrong angle, modern handguard on a vietnam-era ar, etc), or are deliberately comically large/small.

If [[antique firearm]] is applicable to the gun in question, then design faults should (most likely) be considered part of the style and not bad gun anatomy.

h4. See also
* [[anatomical nonsense]]
* [[artistic error]]
* [[bad anatomy]]
* [[bad vehicle anatomy]]
* [[cursed M4A1 (meme)]]
* [[engineering nonsense]]
* [[Tag Group:Image Composition]]

title: jean_bart_(azur_lane)
body:
[[Azur Lane]]'s representation of the French battleship [i]Jean Bart[/i].  Character design by [[Ask (askzy)]], voiced by [[Inoue Marina]].

She is the leader of Vichya Dominion (the game's version of the Vichy French regime), having [[red eyes]], [[long hair|long]], and [[brown hair]] tied in a [[ponytail]].

As her namesake is a historical French [[pirate|privateer]], her design is piratical in theme. Her outfit consists of a [[black jacket]] with gold fringes and [[epaulettes]], [[black dress]], red [[corset]], [[black shorts]], black [[knee boots|knee boot]] to her left and a regular boot to her right, single [[striped legwear|striped]] [[thighhighs|thighhigh]], and a single [[red gloves|red glove]].

Her [[rigging]] is somewhat similar to her sister [[Richelieu (azur lane)|]], albeit her gun coverings are painted black, while she uses 100 mm twin mounts instead of 152 mm triple mounts as a secondary armament. While she also has a bridge structure holding the two sides together, it lacks the [[mast]] and [[radar]]s of her sister for historical reasons. She also carries a large [[French flag]] with the Vichy battle-ax in the middle.



h4. Appearance 

* !post #3202442: Default
* !post #3632576: [[jean bart (uninhibited bloodstone) (azur lane)|Uninhibited Bloodstone]]

title: alfathor_(fire_emblem)
body:
Character from [[Fire Emblem Heroes]].

AlfaÃ°Ã¶r is the creator deity of the setting of Fire Emblem Heroes; he has written the Twilit Runes, which are said to describe the fate of the universe and are absolute in their description. He serves as the main antagonist of Book IX, and is implied to have masterminded all of the story's prior conflicts. [[Loki (Fire Emblem)|Loki]], [[Thorr (Fire Emblem)|ThÃ³rr]], [[Baldr (Fire Emblem Heroes)|Baldr]], [[Hodr (Fire Emblem)|HÃ¶Ã°r]], [[Vali (Fire Emblem)|]] and [[Heimdallr (Fire Emblem)|]] all serve him.

AlfaÃ°Ã¶r appears as a man of [[old man|greatly advanced age]] with [[white hair]], a [[mustache]] and a [[braided beard|braided]] [[beard]]. A [[mask]] adorns his left eye and is part of a [[crown]] on his head. His right eye, which is visible, is [[red eyes|red]] and [[glowing|glows]].

body:

At school, she is described as having an extremely menacing aura, which led to her having few friends. She was once seen beating up her older brother. Because of these things, other students at school became afraid to approach her or get to know her. In truth, she is actually quite shy and it is implied that she is only able to talk to small children. 

After befriending [[Komaru (himouto! umaru-chan)|]], she gradually becomes more social, open and confidant.

Voiced by [[Shiraishi Haruka]]

title: collage_(band)
body: Collage is a Taiwanese band that released their first album in 2021, with two members: lead singer [[Natsuko Lariyod]], who is of mixed Hakka and Amis ancestry, and Hunter Wang, who is of Minnan descent. Mankindâ€™s only hope for survival is to fight their way to a deep space cargo ship and leave the Earth behind. Aliens features a 55 inch LED cabinet, enhanced gun system, eye catching Aliens topper and four frantic levels of non-stop shooting action, with players battling an onslaught of all new alien enemies.

title: mujun-gatamari_(meme)
body:
(ã‚€ã˜ã‚…ã‚“ãŒãŸã¾ã‚Š, lit. "clump of contradictions" or "ball of radical contradictions") also known as é–“é•ã„AA ("wrong ASCII art")

A specific style of [[ASCII art]] that originated on [[2channel]]. It can also be considered a style of [[meme]].

In the most common form, many rows of fixed-width ASCII characters are arranged to depict a [[logo]], above which appears a picture of a character or object, usually with a speech bubble beside it. Artists often make use of [[emphasis lines]] to give context to their subject. The defining feature of this [[meme]] is that no two components of the image can match. Quotes, onomatopoeia, artist [[commentary|commentaries]], tags, [[furigana]], and so on: no matter how many elements go into the image, each one is from a different source. Aside from the text, the picture itself often combines several characters into a kind of [[chimera]]. For example, the earliest known example of this [[ASCII art]] depicts a creature with [[Juushimatsu Juushoku]]'s head and the body of a dog, with a speech bubble saying "meow!!" and the caption "chick".

[[2channel]] users often deploy these pictures to defuse tensions in heated discussion threads full of arguments and flaming. Posting a Mujun-Gatamari usually carries an implicit meaning of "C'mon, you guys, chill out." In these cases, posters often introduce their image with a catchphrase meaning "æ®ºä¼ã¨ã—ãŸã‚¹ãƒ¬ã«~ãŒ!! (Into the bloody fray of this thread, *** has arrived!!)" This usage originated with another [[ASCII art]] character, [[youkan_(food)|Youkan]] Man. Images of cheerful Youkan Man, who keeps on smiling no matter how many times he is cut in half, were once a popular option for calming down flame wars. Now, however, posters eschew this [[ascii art]] as something that just makes everyone angrier.

h4.See also

* [[out of character]] - some of [[out of character]] images on pixiv & NicoSeiga are incorrectly tagged as [[mujun-gatamari (meme)|]].

h4. External links

* "Nicopedia article":http://dic.nicovideo.jp/id/4971717

title: curtains
body:
Curtains are sheets of cloth used for privacy and to block light, usually hung over [[window|windows]].

h2. Curtain Types
* [[Floating curtains]] are curtains fluttering as if blown by wind, such as from an [[open window]].
* [[See-through curtains]] are sheer (translucent) curtains that let light pass freely and don't hide what's behind them.

h2. Curtain Actions
* [[Behind curtains]], when the subject is fully or partially behind a curtain, even if it's see-through.
* [[Curtain grab]], when someone is grabbing a curtain, such as to hide themselves.

h4. See also
* [[Bead curtain]]
* [[Window blinds]]
* [[Noren]]
* [[Canopy bed]]
* [[Privacy screen]]

title: solo:_a_star_wars_story
body:
[b]Solo: A Star Wars Story[/b] is a 2018 American space Western film centering on the [[Star Wars]] character [[Han Solo]]. Directed by Ron Howard, produced by Lucasfilm, and distributed by Walt Disney Studios Motion Pictures, it is the second Star Wars anthology film, following [[Rogue One: A Star Wars Story]] (2016). 

[[Alden Ehrenreich]] stars as Solo, with [[Woody Harrelson]], [[Emilia Clarke]], [[Donald Glover]], [[Thandiwe Newton]], [[Phoebe Waller-Bridge]], [[Joonas Suotamo]], and [[Paul Bettany]].

The film tells the origin story of Han Solo and [[Chewbacca]], who join a heist within the criminal underworld ten years prior to the events of [[Star Wars: A New Hope]] (1977).

title: gelgoog_hmt_johnny_ridden_custom
body:
A fictional manned giant robot from the [[Gundam]] [[mecha]]verse. 

[b]MS-14B Gelgoog High Mobility Type (Johnny Ridden Custom)[/b]

An even higher performing version of the already fantastic [[Gelgoog]] for use by select ace pilots. One of those few was the Crimson Lightning, Johnny Ridden, who had his unit painted in his trademark red - again, constantly being mistaken for [[Char Aznable]] in the battlefield. His unit was different in the presence of a backpack and the deeper shade of red with a black torso. 

Ironically enough, this constant confusion seemed to help Char, as during the Battle of [[A Baoa Qu]] the Federation troops attacked the red Gelgoog believing it to be the Red Comet, while the real one handled the [[Zeong]].

title: gelgoog_vertex
body:
A fictional manned giant robot from the [[Gundam]] [[mecha]]verse. It appears in [[MSV-R: The Return of Johnny Ridden]].

[b]MS-14J/BR Gelgoog Vertex[/b]

A modified [[Gelgoog]] High Mobility Type that essentially has the shoulder binders and backpack of a [[ReGelg]] grafted onto it, giving it fantastic mobility.

See [[traditional Greek clothes]] for Greek clothing after the 6th century AD.

h4. Clothes

title: nijigasaki_school_uniform
body:
The [[school uniform]] worn by students of Nijigasaki High School (è™¹ãƒ¶å’²å­¦åœ’) in [[Love Live! School idol festival]] and [[Love Live! Nijigasaki High School Idol Club]]. It comes in 2 main variants; a winter version and a summer version. Additionally, most characters add personal touches to their uniform, like omitting or replacing certain pieces, adding extra layers, etc. Specific changes to the uniform are listed on the respective character's page.

The [[winter uniform]] consists of a [[black jacket]] with golden [[buttons]], a [[white shirt|white]] [[long sleeves|long-sleeved]]  [[collared shirt|collared]] [[dress shirt]] and a [[grey skirt|grey]] or [[white skirt|white]] [[pleated skirt|pleated]] [[plaid skirt|plaid]] [[miniskirt]].

The [[summer uniform]] consists of a [[black vest|black]] [[vest]] or [[yellow sweater vest|yellow]] [[sweater vest]], a [[short sleeves|short-sleeved]] [[white shirt|white]] or [[blue shirt|light blue]] [[collared shirt]] and a [[blue skirt|navy blue]] [[pleated skirt|pleated]] [[plaid skirt|plaid]] [[miniskirt]].

Both versions feature a [[neck ribbon]] with the color indicating the year of the student, ([[yellow ribbon|yellow]] for first years, [[red ribbon|red]]/[[pink ribbon|pink]] for second years, and [[green ribbon|green]] for third years).

h4. Examples

title: okazaki_yumemi
body:
Okazaki Yumemi (å²¡å´å¤¢ç¾) is the canonical final boss of the third [[Touhou]] game æ±æ–¹å¤¢æ™‚ç©º ã€œ The Phantasmagoria of Dim.Dream ("canonical" because it's a dueling shooter, so everyone fights everyone anyway). 

An eighteen-year-old university probability physics professor from the future who got shunned by society for believing in magic, she comes to Gensokyo to capture its specimens and prove her theory is right. A genius even by the future's high standards, she's the creator of the [[Probability Space Hypervessel]] - something not only capable of travel between time and space, but also of ripping through the Great Hakurei Barrier.

Yumemi's outfit and appearance is primarily red: her eyes, hair, vest, skirt, [i]and[/i] her cape are all red.  Even the bow on her white blouse is red.  Commonly, she will be represented by a red cross motif in reference to her in-game attacks; or strawberries, in reference to her theme music, [i]Strawberry Crisis!![/i]

She will often be seen with her assistant and fellow scientist, [[Kitashirakawa Chiyuri]].

h4. See also

* Touhou Wiki: http://en.touhouwiki.net/wiki/Yumemi_Okazaki

title: gunpla_boy_(ishiyumi)
body:
å°‘å¹´
[tn]"Boy"[/tn]

Deuteragonist of "The Goddess of the G-Spring":[/pools/17110], an original Twitter-hosted web series by [[Kato Takuji]]. He is the principal viewpoint character of the series, acting as the audience surrogate.

Originally a casual fan of [[Gunpla]] (introduced to him by the Gundam Build series) before meeting the [[G-Spring Goddess_(ishiyumi)|]]. Gets more and more into both Gundam (the various series) and Gunpla as the story progresses, under her 'tutelage'.

[[G-Forest Goddess (ishiyumi)|]] has tried to convert him into the world of [[Gundam|SD Gundam]] (and becoming her follower) several times over the course of the series, with varying degrees of success.

[[Little Lass (ishiyumi)|]] is his childhood friend from the same village. She's constantly trying to prevent (and later cockblocking) him from meeting the goddesses, for various reasons (first concern, then jealousy, and finally madness).

title: g-forest_goddess_(ishiyumi)
body:
[tn]"The Goddess of the Forest of G"[/tn]

Tritagonist of "The Goddess of the G-Spring":[/pools/17110], an original Twitter-hosted web series by [[Kato Takuji]].

A hardcore fan of [[Gundam|SD Gundam]]. Among the other goddesses, she's the one with the most common sense.

[[G-Spring Goddess (ishiyumi)|]] is her rival, with whom she often engages in fistfights over Gundam discussions and other topics. She always wins due to type advantage ([[pokemon|Pokemon]] style: grass beats water) and being more powerful in general.

Has no personal attachment to [[Gunpla Boy (ishiyumi)|]], but try to convert him as a follower anyway. Either due to her personal crusade of spreading the SD Gundam series, or annoying the G-Spring Goddess, or both.

Just like the characters in her beloved SD Gundam series, she can change between two forms: her petite, flat-chested form (SD: Super Deformed) and her tall, big-breasted form (RF: Real Form). The latter is rarely used, only shown occasionally to annoy the G-Spring Goddess.

title: norio_tomokawa_(mental_omega)
body: Norio Tomokawa is the Japanese born hero of the Pacific Front Subfaction (comprised out of Japan, South Korea, the Philippines, Indonesia, Australia, and New Zealand) of the Allied Nations in the Mental Omega mod for Red Alert 2: Yuri's Revenge. Making use of a suit of flight capable powered armour, he fights with a cryobeam projector and a seemingly unlimited number of high impact seeker missiles capable of attacking both ranged and ground targets. Though he served with distinction during the third world war (though ultimately failing to stop the Sino-Soviet invasion of Japan as part of the ultimate Soviet victory in that war) and in the following Mental Omega War against Yuri's Epsilon Army, he would be killed in the final allied battle at Antarctica by Libra, whose vast psychic powers were too much for simple skill and gear to overcome.

title: head_out_of_frame
body:
When the main subject's head is fully or partially cropped out of frame, but their torso is still in the frame. The head may be only halfway out of frame. The nose and mouth may be visible, but not the eyes.

The main emphasis should be on a single character's torso. Do not use this tag for [[faceless]] or mostly [[out of frame]] background characters, or for [[close-up|close-ups]] or a character's [[ass]] or [[lower body]]. This tag is for when the main subject's head is cropped out of the frame, not most or all of their body.

title: yanqing_(honkai:_star_rail)
body:
A playable character in [[Honkai: Star Rail]]. Voiced by [[Inoue Marina]] in Japanese.  

General [[Jing Yuan]]'s retainer. A gifted swordsman who hasn't even come of age. No one can best Yanqing when he holds a sword in hand. 

He is portrayed with [[long hair|long]] [[blonde hair]] with an [[ahoge]], and [[yellow eyes]]. His default outfit consists of a [[white shirt]], [[white pants]], [[blue robe]] with [[jingle bell]]s and Cloud Knight badges pinned on the left side, black [[vambraces]], and [[white boots|white]] [[ankle boots]]. 

h4. Costumes
* !post #7691264: Splash art
* !post #7484069: [[yanqing_(star_rail_live_2024)_(honkai:_star_rail)|Star Rail Live 2024]]

h4. Profile
[expand]
The spirited lieutenant of the Xianzhou Luofu, and also its most proficient swordsman.

He is born for swords and obsessed with them. Whenever a sword rests in his hand, none would dare to underestimate this genius still in the early days of his youth.

Perhaps the only thing capable of dulling his treasured blade's sharp edge is time. 
[/expand]

h4. See also
* [[Ma Yanqing]] - his [[Honkai Impact 3rd]] counterpart.

title: lumiora_lumen

title: pop-up_headlights
body:
Headlights for [[car]]s that are hidden and flip or rotate into position when engaged. While they were often seen in [[sports car]]s in the 90s and earlier for the aerodynamic benefit while disengaged, they ultimately fell out of use due to advancements in fixed headlight design and stricter pedestrian safety requirements in certain regions.

The last major production car to feature this design trait was the [[chevrolet corvette c5|C5]] [[Chevrolet Corvette]]. Certain models with pop-ups (primarily Japanese cars from the 80s and 90s) are commonly modified so that the headlights only open a portion of the way. Pop-ups modified in this manner are often referred to as "sleepy eye" headlights.

This tag is only for posts that depict pop-up headlights in the engaged position.

h4. Examples
* !post #6660312: [[Mazda RX-7 FD|FD RX-7]] with pop-ups engaged
* !post #7217058: [[Mazda MX-5 NA|NA MX-5]] with pop-ups engaged and [[headlight beam]]s
* !post #6466322: [[Toyota Sprinter Trueno]] with a [[single pop-up headlight]] engaged
* !post #7941877: [[Nissan 180SX]] with sleepy eye pop-ups

body:
The first-known Fanged Wyvern of the [[Monster Hunter (series)|]] series, as well as flagship monster of [[Monster Hunter Portable 3rd]].

Known as the "Thunder Wolf Wyvern", the Zinogre resembles a blue-scaled [[wolf]] with horns, sharp claws, a huge tail, and spikes on its back which stick out when enraged. Originally an "adventurer-raising" simulator with auto-battling RPG elements using the [[School Girl Strikers]] engine, it features 36 fully voiced characters designed by [[blade_(galaxist)|Blade]].

The game terminated its online service on November 1, 2017, but remained available by transitioning to an offline mode, where the stories can be viewed and the characters interacted with. title: flash
body:
[b]As of March 31, 2021, uploading flash files is no longer possible.[/b] See forum #183397 for details.

This tag is for games, [[music video]]s, and [[animated|animations]] created using [[adobe animate (medium)|Adobe Flash]], as SWF files to be played with Flash Player.

While Flash enjoyed success from the late 1990s to the late 2000s (especially because of the failure of the Java platform in the web), it eventually declined as JavaScript and other browser-agnostic platforms like HTML5 and WebGL matured. Adobe, recognizing that Flash lost its relevance over time, announced in 2017 that in-browser Flash plugins would no longer be supported after December 2020; all major browsers permanently removed Flash support by the end of January 2021.

During its lifetime, Adobe made a change to the Flash player after version 9 that broke many older files. As of now, the 51 posts with this tag have been fixed by flipping a flag in the header, as detailed in topic #15331, but if such a file was found, it was recommended to try and view it in version 9's stand-alone player.

As of March 2021, Danbooru is set up to automatically load all Flash posts using Ruffle.js, which uses "WebAssembly":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/WebAssembly] to emulate Flash in modern browsers as a part of the broader "Ruffle Project":[https://ruffle.rs]. While this means you can view Flash posts without falling back on an outdated browser that's old enough to still support the original Flash Player, please keep in mind that Ruffle's core emulation of Flash [b]is still in an alpha state[/b] and it's less likely to work with files that are newer and/or more complex. See [[ruffle compatible]] for posts that have been manually confirmed to work with the version of Ruffle.js that Danbooru is currently using.

h4. See also

* [[sound]]
* [[audible music]]
* [[audible speech]]
* [[Tag group:Image composition]]
* [[Adobe Flash]]

h4. External links

* "Wikipedia: Adobe Flash Player":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adobe_Flash_Player]
* "Ruffle: Official website":[https://ruffle.rs]

title: type_96_aa_gun
body:
The [b]Type 96[/b] 25mm [[autocannon]] was the standard medium-range [[anti-aircraft gun]] of the [[Imperial Japanese Navy]], and was used in single, double, and even triple barrel mounts on all Japanese vessels. It was also used as a dual-purpose anti-aircraft and anti-tank weapon on fixed mounts in land bases. 

Based on a French Hochkiss design from the mid-1930s, the Type 96 struggled to keep pace with increasing aircraft speed and armor developments of the late 1930s into the start of [[World War II]], and during the war often required multiple batteries working in concert to down single Allied aircrafts. Nevertheless, the lack of available alternatives kept the Type 96 as the main Japanese AA weapon through the war. 

h4. See also
* [[Type 93 HMG]] A 13mm machine gun used as light AA, that by the end of the war was mostly replaced by single-barrel versions of the Type 96.
* [[Bofors 40 mm gun]] The Allied equivalent of the Type 96, as a medium-range AA gun. 

h4. External links
* "Wikipedia: Type 96 AA gun":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Type_96_25_mm_AT/AA_gun

title: belafu
body:
Belafu is a character from [[Made In Abyss]].

He is one of the Three Sages of Ilblu. As [[belafu_(human)|human]], he used to be one of the key members of the Ganja Suicide Corps and is now one of Ilblu's most important residents.

Belaf has a long, centipede-like body and a head reminiscent of a flower. He has almost no facial features except for what is at first glance two empty eye sockets, but are actually more akin to mouths. A proboscis-like tube protrudes from each hole to eat and his voice also comes from these openings.

title: jirai_kei
body:
A fashion subculture for "landmine-type" girls that originated in Japan's "KabukichÅ":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kabukich%C5%8D] district and first spread in popularity in early 2020.

Fashion consists of two sides: é‡ç”£å‹ (ryousangata, literally "mass production") - a more mainstream girly style, and ã‚µãƒ–ã‚«ãƒ« (subculture) - the more alternative and dark variant. Do note that the latter term is also used for alternative fashion in general.

Ryousangata tends to use a lot of pink with some black accents, and often uses frilly [[blouse]]s, [[suspender skirt]]s, [[choker]]s, heart decorations, [[bow]]s, [[platform shoes]], and [[ankle socks]].

Subculture jirai, on the other hand, leans towards darker color palettes such as black, grey, red, and white. [[layered clothes|Layered clothing]] is common, as are [[chain]]s, striped patterns, fishnets, [[leg warmers]], [[track jacket]]s, and [[boots]].

Both sides of the fashion use makeup that accentuates the [[aegyo sal]] and gives the face a "sickly-cute" appearance.

title: merchandise
body:
Depictions of products based on media franchises such as anime, video games or music. Often, though not inherently, depictions of actual real world merchandise that exists.

This may involve characters with merchandise of their own series, or characters with merchandise from other series (often as a visual easter egg).

title: itabag
body:
A term for [[shoulder bag|shoulder bags]] and [[backpack|backpacks]] extensively covered in anime merchandise. Most commonly, these have a plastic window where merchandise can be displayed inside.

They are a common aspect of [[oshi-katsu]], where they are decorated with merchandise of a particular idol or character.

Most often, they feature a large number of [[button badge]]s, and may even have small [[character doll]]s placed inside.

title: monica_von_ochs
body:
A non playable character in [[Fire Emblem: Three Houses]]. A student from Garreg Mach Monastery. 

She hails from the Adrestian Empire (being from the previous Black Eagles group) and is quite fond of [[Edelgard_von_Hresvelg|Edelgard]].

[spoiler]The real Monica von Ochs is never encountered in-game in Three Houses, as she is killed and impersonated by the assassin [[kronya_(fire_emblem)|Kronya]] prior to the events of the story.[/spoiler]

[spoiler]However, in [[Fire Emblem Warriors: Three Hopes]], she appears in the flesh when she is saved from Kronya by [[shez_(fire_emblem)|Shez]]. Monica then becomes a playable character for Edelgard's story, Scarlet Blaze. She possesses a minor Crest of Macuil and is specialized in wind magic as a result.[/spoiler]

title: himekaji
body:
Style of popular Japanese [[fashion]] that evolved from [[Hime Gyaru]] - originally being a gyaru substyle, though nowadays it has become detached from gyaru. The name means "princess casual", and it is considered to be a part of the wider umbrella of "girly kei". In Japan, it is also called Kanayan style, after the model who popularized it.

Himekaji uses a color palette primarily consisting of pinks, whites, and tans. [[Pom pom (clothes)|]] decorations and [[fur trim]]s are common, as are [[rhinestone]]s and [[floral print]]. Popular brands in the style include [[Liz Lisa]], [[DearMyLove (brand)|]], and [[Ank Rouge]].

It is sometimes confused for the ryousangata side of [[jirai kei]].

title: teenage_mutant_ninja_turtles_(mirage_comics)
body:
A comic book series that began the [[Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles]] franchise. Originally intended to as a one-shot comic, but due to its popularity it became an ongoing series.

Notable for its black and white format and darker tone compared to the rest of the adaptations that followed, the series follows the exploits of four genetically-mutated turtles who were trained under the orders of [[Master Splinter]], a pet rat, to combat various foes, most notably involving the likes of the Foot clan and their leader Oroku Saki, who secretly takes on the identity of the [[Shredder (TMNT)|]].

h4. External links

* "Wikipedia: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles (Mirage Studios)":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Teenage_Mutant_Ninja_Turtles_(Mirage_Studios)]

title: balan_wonderworld
body:
A platforming video game developed by Arzest and Balan Company, published by [[Square Enix]], and released for [[PlayStation 4]], [[PlayStation 5]], [[Xbox One]], [[Xbox Series X]], [[Nintendo Switch]], and [[computer|PC]] on March 26, 2021.

Despite seemingly having a dream team behind the game with [[Sonic (series)|]] creator Naka Yuji helming the project as director, [[Ooshima Naoto]] providing original character designs, and Square Enix's trademark CGI cutscene quality, the game was largely criticized upon release due to it's questionably simple gameplay, useless powerups, and subpar level design.

h4. External links

* "Wikipedia: Balan Wonderworld":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Balan_Wonderworld]

title: taguel
body:
A race introduced in [[Fire Emblem Awakening]].  

Similar in nature to the manakete (dragon) race, taguel typically inhabit a weaker human-like body and temporarily transform into a giant beast similar to a monster bunny using the power of their beaststones when fighting. Taguels have been persecuted by humans and driven to the brink of extinction, by the time of Awakening the last living taguel is [[panne (fire emblem)|Panne]].

[spoiler][[yarne (fire emblem)| Yarne]], as the son of [[panne (fire emblem)|Panne]], makes them the only two known living taguels. [/spoiler]

title: tacet_discord_(wuthering_waves)
body:
Tacet Discords (TDs) are the non-human enemy species of [[Wuthering Waves]]. They are sentient beings formed by chaotic frequency energy that are designed to feed on other frequencies to stabilise and evolve. TDs used by resonators or human civilisations such as Rinascita are alternatively called Echoes to differentiate them from their hostile counterparts.

There are four ranks of Tacet Discords: Calamity, Overlord, Elite and Common. They also possess different classifications based on the frequencies they primarily consume: Whisperin (human-shaped bodies), Howler (flora and fauna), Tranquilite (earth and other inorganic matter such as rocks and crystal formations), Staticoid (parasitic upon man-made objects) and Clamorlings (unknown classification to date).

Lord above all Tacet Discords are Threnodians who seek to destroy civilisations, who are the direct counterparts of Sentinels who guide civilisations.

h4. Threnodians/Sentinels

- [[Jue (Wuthering Waves)|]]: Jinzhou Sentinel
- [[Imperator (Wuthering Waves)|]]: Rinascita Sentinel
- [[Leviathan (Wuthering Waves)|]]: Rinascitan Threnodian of Assimilation

title: new_york_excelsior
body: The New York Excelsior (often stylized as NYXL) was an American professional Overwatch esports team based in New York City. The Excelsior competed in the Overwatch League (OWL) as a member of the league's West region. Founded in 2017, the team was one of twelve founding members of the Overwatch League and was the first professional esports team to represent the city of New York.

title: tr-6_woundwort
body:
A fictional manned military giant robot from the [[Gundam]] [[mecha]]verse.

[b]RX-124 Gundam TR-6 [Woundwort][/b]

The final TR Series [[mobile_suit|MS]] produced by the [[titans_(gundam)|Titans]] Test Team. title: anti-aqua
body:
The [[corruption|corrupted]] [[Dark_persona|form]] of [[Aqua_(kingdom_hearts)|Aqua]] after being defeated by [[Ansem Seeker Of Darkness]] and being thrown into the seas of the Dark Margin.
Her hair is a bleached blue, her eyes are yellow, and her once-white dress has darkened and become tattered. title: galleon_(granblue_fantasy)
body:
[[Granblue Fantasy]] character. One of the Six Dragons, Galleon (full title [b]Galleon the Gold[/b]) is the Dragon of Earth.

Incensed by how the landmass occupied by all who live under the skies is so much more miniscule than it was originally meant to be, she laments the hardships that skydwellers are forced to endure. Harboring compassion as bounteous as the earth itself, she chooses to live beside mankind to better understand their plight and to change along with the world.

title: white_queen
body:
A fictional character who appears in Lewis Carroll's 1871 fantasy novel [i]Through the Looking-Glass[/i], the sequel to [[Alice's Adventures in Wonderland]]. In John Tenniel's original illustrations she is depicted with a [[crown]] resembling the head of a queen chess piece and skirt resembling the base of a chess piece.

In Tim Burton's film adaptation of [[Alice in Wonderland (Tim Burton)|]] and sequel [i]Through the Looking-Glass (2016)[/i] she is given the name [[Mirana of Marmoreal]] and is depicted as a beautiful young woman with whitish blonde hair, black eyebrows, and with black nail polish.

title: multicolored_clothes
body:
Clothing that prominently features two or more distinct colors. For example, a red-and-blue dress.

* White, black, and grey don't count. For example, blue-and-white striped thighhighs don't count.
* Multiple shades of the same color don't count. For example, a light-blue-and-dark-blue shirt doesn't count.
* Trim, bows, or other decorations don't count.
* Simple two-color [[argyle]], [[plaid]], [[polka dot]], [[checkered]], [[gradient]], print, or other patterns that have their own tags don't count.

In essence, multicolored clothes need to have unusual colors and styles that pop out visually to the viewer.

h4. Examples

* !post #2542430: Orange-and-brown striped thighhighs
* !post #2328916: Red-and-green checkered skirt
* !post #5361051: Red, pink, and yellow argyle shirt
* !post #2108655: Three color polka dot sarong and bikini
* !post #2106871: [[Hecatia Lapislazuli]]'s red, green, and blue plaid skirt
* !post #2710747: [[Souryuu Asuka Langley]]'s red-and-orange [[test plugsuit (evangelion)|]]

title: murao_mira
body:
[b]Murao Mira[/b] is a playable character in [[Alice Gear Aegis]].

In her daily life, she wears the [[Kamihama University Affiliated School uniform]] paired with [[black thighhighs|black]] [[thighhighs]].

As a [[Magical Girl]], she wears a [[white flower|white]] [[hair flower|flower]], a [[blue ribbon|blue]] [[tress ribbon|tress]] [[hair ribbon|ribbon]], a [[blue choker|blue]] [[choker]], a [[blue gemstone|blue]] [[chest jewel]], a [[short kimono|short]] [[white kimono|white]]  (or with a pair of [[shoulder cutout]]s) [[right-over-left kimono|right-over-left]] [[kimono]] worn [[off shoulder|hanging off her arms]] with [[long sleeves|long]] [[wide sleeves]] and its [[hooded kimono|hood]] [[hood down|down]], a [[short dress|short]] [[black dress|black]] [[dress]]/[[black shirt|black]] [[sleeveless shirt|shirt]] with [[spaghetti strap|spaghetti]] [[sleeveless dress|straps]], a [[white bow|white]] [[waist bow]], a [[thigh strap]], [[single thighhigh|single]] [[black thighhighs|black]] [[thighhighs|thighhigh]], and [[white boots|white]] [[ankle boots|ankle]] [[boots]]. title: muted_asria
body:
An [[indie virtual youtuber|independent]] [[virtual youtuber|VTuber]] and [[VRChat]] mute streamer from Mexico, who began activities in late 2019. Known for her highly interactive streams and charity events. Founder of the vtuber group H.U.M.A.N.S., one of the earliest and biggest in the Spanish-speaking community. Her main model was called "[[android|Robo]][[cat girl|neko]]", that featured [[white hair]], [[blue eyes]], [[mechanical_ears |mechanical]] [[cat ears]], and a USB [[cable tail]], wearing a [[white shirt]], [[black sweater vest]], [[grey skirt]], [[paw gloves]] and [[paw shoes|paw boots]]

Somewhen in late 2020, it was discovered that her tragic background and medical expenses weren't real, and that the streamer was a guy, all of which caused big uproar in the community. In late 2021, the streamer behind Asria tried to make a comeback as [[Koroyn]] targeting the English-speaking community.

Around that time, the Asria character was transferred to another individual, who began activities in 2022.

title: denkou_choujin_gridman:_boys_invent_great_hero
body:
[b]Denkou Choujin Gridman: boys invent great hero[/b] is the ninth short featured in the [[Japan Animator Expo]]. It is based off of the live action series [[Denkou Choujin Gridman]].

The entire short took place 22 years after Gridman's final battle with [[Kahn Digifier]]. [[Toudou Takeshi]], a former brainwashed servant of Kahn, reflects on the past incidents as monster attacks took place in real life. Using the Acceptor, he transforms into [[Gridman Sigma]] before facing the monster.
